sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS(edge)
    participant OAuth as oauth-proxy sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as JupyterLab Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Elyra as Elyra Pipeline Editor<br/>(in notebook)
    participant DSP as Data Science Pipelines API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant S3 as S3-compatible Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Kustomize as Kustomize Apply
    participant OSAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Quay as quay.io/modh/*<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Accesses Notebook Workbench

    User->>Route: GET https://{notebook}-{ns}.apps.{cluster}<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS edge termination
    Route->>OAuth: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS
    Note right of OAuth: OAuth2 token validation<br/>OpenShift OAuth
    OAuth->>Jupyter: Forward authenticated request<br/>HTTP/8888, plaintext (localhost)
    Note right of Jupyter: ServerApp.token='' (empty)<br/>Trusts oauth-proxy
    Jupyter-->>OAuth: Notebook UI response
    OAuth-->>Route: Encrypted response
    Route-->>User: HTTPS response

    Note over Elyra,S3: Flow 2: Notebook Submits Pipeline via Elyra

    Elyra->>DSP: POST pipeline submission<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer token (SA cert)
    DSP-->>Elyra: Pipeline run ID
    Note right of DSP: Pipeline runtime executes
    DSP->>S3: Store/retrieve artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS credentials
    S3-->>DSP: Artifacts

    Note over Kustomize,Quay: Flow 3: ImageStream Registration

    Kustomize->>OSAPI: Apply ImageStream manifests<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    OSAPI-->>Kustomize: Resources created
    Note right of OSAPI: ImageStream created with<br/>SHA256-pinned image refs
    OSAPI->>Quay: Resolve image references<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: None (public images)
    Quay-->>OSAPI: Image metadata
